edu.iastate.ansci.flip.database

Class PopulationsBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.iastate.ansci.flip.database.PopulationsBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PopulationsBean
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Auxiliary class that creates the options to manage FLIP populations. These operations are intended to be used only by instructors or administrators. An instructor or administrator can do the followings :
    1. Load
      2. Make a selected persistent population to become active. An active population is moved to temporal database. Any future update is executed in the temporal and persistent databases.
    2. Loadcopy
      3. Copy the selected persistent population into the temporal databases.
      Any future update is done only on the temporal database. User explicitly needs to save this copy in permanent database to preserve it. After this copy is saved, any new update is updated at the temporal and persistent databases.
    3. delete
      4. Remove the selected population from persistent database. If the population is also active, the copy at the temporal database is NOT removed.
    4. rename
      5. Update the name of a selected population.
    5. export
      6. Export a selected population into a zip file.
    6. share
      7. Grant/remove the access to a selected population for other instructors
    7. unlock
      8. Release lock of a selected population if this one is still accidently locked and no one is accessing it (This operation is only available for an administrator)
    Author:
    patricio
